Step 5: Try a Failing Assertion (Optional but Useful)
To really understand how assertions work, deliberately break one and observe the failure output:
java@Test
public void testFailingAssertion() {
    assertEquals(10, 2 + 2); // this will fail: expected 10, got 4
}
Run it — you'll see something like:
java.lang.AssertionError: expected:<10> but was:<4>
This is useful because it teaches you how to read JUnit failure messages, which you'll rely on constantly in real projects.
